  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A new GlideScope videolaryngoscope has been developed, which utilizes a track on the superior
      surface of the blade to guide the endotracheal tube, which is advanced in the track as
      opposed to &quot;free-hand&quot; along the inferior surface, where the camera is located. This new
      GlideScope can be used for double-lumen endotracheal tubes (DLT). The investigators
      hypothesize that this GlideScope will be easier to use than the Macintosh blade.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
